cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using Symmetric Positive Definite (SPD) matrices and Riemannian manifolds, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves random projections, which are often used in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve face recognition, person re-identification, and texture classification, which are all subfields of multimedia (cs.MM).
